Output & Saving

--> Save as Normal Text
nmap -oN scan.txt <target>
Saves output in a human-readable format.
Use when: You want a simple report you can read.

--> Save as XML
nmap -oX scan.xml <target>
Saves output in XML format.
Use when: Feeding results into other security tools.

--> Save as Grepable
nmap -oG scan.gnmap <target>
Saves in a format that's easy to search with grep.
Use when: Processing results with scripts later.

--> Save in All Formats
nmap -oA scan <target>
Creates three files: scan.nmap, scan.xml, scan.gnmap.
Use when: Best practice â€” covers all your needs at once.

--> Verbose Output
nmap -v <target>
Shows what nmap is doing in real time.
Use when: You want to see progress during the scan.

--> Extra Verbose
nmap -vv <target>
Even more detail than -v.
Use when: Debugging or learning how nmap works.

--> Show Reason for Port State
nmap --reason <target>
Tells you why nmap marked a port as open/closed/filtered.
Use when: You want to understand the results better.
